    <section>
        <h2>Who Is Nordic Spirit?</h2>
        <p>Nordic Spirit is the UK's dominant nicotine pouch brand, manufactured by <strong>JTI (Japan Tobacco International)</strong> since its launch in Sweden in 2018. JTI is a major global tobacco company with operations across 70+ countries and strict adherence to EU tobacco product regulations (TPD 2014/40/EU). The brand has become synonymous with quality and consistency across Scandinavia and the United Kingdom, offering a curated selection of subtle, well-balanced flavours that appeal to both newcomers and experienced users.</p>
        <p>What sets Nordic Spirit apart is its philosophy: <strong>refined taste experiences designed for smooth, sustained enjoyment</strong> rather than sensational gimmicks. Every flavour is carefully formulated for balanced flavour delivery.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Brand History & JTI's Legacy</h2>
        <p>Japan Tobacco International launched Nordic Spirit in 2018, tapping into Sweden's established snus culture and expanding into the whitening nicotine pouch category. The brand was strategically designed for European consumers seeking a contemporary alternative to traditional snus, with particular emphasis on <strong>mild, fruity profiles for mainstream appeal</strong>.</p>
        <p>JTI's backing ensured rigorous quality control, consistent manufacturing, and rapid market expansion. By 2022, Nordic Spirit had become the UK's fastest-growing nicotine pouch brand. Today, it commands approximately 35% of the UK market—a testament to brand trust and product consistency. As reported by industry analysts and EU tobacco regulators, Nordic Spirit's market dominance reflects its effective positioning.</p>
        <p>JTI's experience across tobacco, snus, and heat-not-burn products means Nordic Spirit benefits from decades of flavour science and user research. For context on legal requirements, see our guide on <a href="/blog/nicotine-pouches-legal-europe-2026">nicotine pouch regulations across Europe</a>.</p>
    </section>

