    <section>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <h3>1. Are Nordic Spirit pouches safe?</h3>
        <p>Nordic Spirit pouches contain nicotine—a highly addictive substance—but no tobacco. They carry no cancer risk equivalent to cigarette smoking. They are legal and age-restricted (18+) in the UK. If you have heart conditions, pregnancy concerns, or nicotine sensitivity, consult your GP before use.</p>

        <h3>2. How long does one Nordic Spirit pouch last?</h3>
        <p>Typically 30–45 minutes. Nicotine release is gradual, so satisfaction is sustained without sharp peaks or crashes. You'll sense when the flavour and nicotine are depleted and naturally remove it.</p>

        <h3>3. Can I swallow saliva with Nordic Spirit?</h3>
        <p>Yes, saliva produced during use is safe to swallow. Nordic Spirit generates minimal drip, so swallowing is not a concern. Some users prefer to spit (as with traditional snus); others simply swallow.</p>

        <h3>4. Which Nordic Spirit flavour is most popular?</h3>
        <p>Mint is the bestseller globally, followed by Spearmint and Bergamot Wildberry. However, "best" is subjective—we recommend starting with classic Mint or Spearmint and exploring from there. Visit <a href="/brands/nordic-spirit">Nordic Spirit products</a> to see current stock.</p>

        <h3>5. Can I use Nordic Spirit if I've never smoked?</h3>
        <p>Technically yes, but it's not recommended. Nicotine pouches are designed for smokers transitioning away from cigarettes or existing snus users. If you're a non-smoker, nicotine carries addiction risk and no health benefit. If you're curious about nicotine or looking to quit smoking, speak to your GP or visit the NHS stop-smoking service.</p>
